Given the function \(a_n = \frac{1}{\log_n 2002}\):

1. Use change of base formula to rewrite \(a_n\)
2. Calculate \( b = a_2 + a_3 + a_4 + a_5 \)
3. Calculate \( c = a_{10} + a_{11} + a_{12} + a_{13} + a_{14} \)
4. Find \( b - c \)

First, let us convert \(a_n\) using the change of base formula:

\[
\log_n 2002 = \frac{\log 2002}{\log n}
\]

Thus,

\[
a_n = \frac{1}{\log_n 2002} = \frac{1}{\frac{\log 2002}{\log n}} = \frac{\log n}{\log 2002}
\]

Next, compute \( b \):

\[
b = a_2 + a_3 + a_4 + a_5
= \frac{\log 2}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 3}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 4}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 5}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 2 + \log 3 + \log 4 + \log 5}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log (2 \cdot 3 \cdot 4 \cdot 5)}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 120}{\log 2002}
\]

Now, compute \( c \):

\[
c = a_{10} + a_{11} + a_{12} + a_{13} + a_{14}
= \frac{\log 10}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 11}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 12}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 13}{\log 2002} + \frac{\log 14}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 10 + \log 11 + \log 12 + \log 13 + \log 14}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log (10 \cdot 11 \cdot 12 \cdot 13 \cdot 14)}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 240240}{\log 2002}
\]

Finally, find \( b - c \):

\[
b - c = \frac{\log 120}{\log 2002} - \frac{\log 240240}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 120 - \log 240240}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log \left( \frac{120}{240240} \right)}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log \left( \frac{1}{2002} \right)}{\log 2002}
= \frac{\log 2002^{-1}}{\log 2002}
= \frac{-\log 2002}{\log 2002}
= -1
\]

